content:
Set up your organization to use the Sales Analytics by enabling CRM Analytics and assigning permission sets to users.

Each Sales Analytics license is a single-user license that provides access to Sales Analytics. It includes a single Sales Analytics app single-user license.

Sales Analytics Data Storage Limits:
- Sales Analytics Apps: 25 million rows
- Analytics Cloud - Additional Data Rows: 100 million rows

To give administrators or users in your org access to the Sales Analytics, enable CRM Analytics and assign ready-made permission sets to them. Assign the Sales Analytics Admin permission set sparingly because it lets users administer Sales Analytics.

Enable Analytics in Salesforce Setup by entering "Analytics" in the QuickFind field and clicking Enable Analytics.

Assign permission sets:
- For administrator-level access: Manage Permission Sets, check boxes next to user names, assign and done
- For user-level access: same steps but for Sales Analytics User

Create and share Sales Analytics with users in your organization after completing these steps. Users can only explore dashboards and datasets after sharing the app.
title: Configuring User Permissions for Salesforce Sales Analytics
